  "name": "Search/date",
  "description": "Date search conformance tests that complement Search/intervals.json (which already covers the 8 date prefixes eq/ne/gt/lt/ge/le/sa/eb representatively). This suite covers scenarios NOT exercised by intervals.json: ANDing two repeated date params to form a range, matching a point-in-time query against an Observation with an effectivePeriod, invalid/out-of-range date literals rejected with 400, and the FHIR R4 partial-precision date-equality ambiguity (overlap vs. containment) documented in Microsoft's DateSearchTests.cs as AB#191826 — servers legitimately differ here, so those specific assertions are warningOnly. Ported from fhir-server's DateSearchTests.cs / DateSearchTestFixture.cs.",
